      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54B32 3.2L inline-six engine with high-pressure double VANOS and individual throttle bodies. This specimen is mated to a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission, delivering power through a factory M-variable limited-slip differential. The vehicle has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance, including documented rod bearing replacement and a proactive rear subframe reinforcement to ensure structural integrity under high-torque loads. The suspension retains its original geometry with zero bushing deflection, providing the communicative steering feel these chassis are renowned for. The exterior finish is flawless, and the interior shows no wear on the bolsters or trim. This is an investment-grade enthusiast's car with complete service history and zero mechanical compromises.",
